# Design System: shadcn/ui

All UI in this project must be built using **shadcn/ui** components.

## Rules

- Always use shadcn/ui components (`Button`, `Card`, `Dialog`, `Input`, `Select`, etc.) instead of building custom components or using other UI libraries
- Follow shadcn/ui conventions for theming, variants, and composition
- When a needed component exists in shadcn/ui, install and use it — never recreate it manually
- Use `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Style with Tailwind CSS classes only — use Tailwind's built-in color palette
- Never use arbitrary hex values in className — all custom colors are defined as CSS variables

## Adding Components

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

## Example

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<button className="bg-[#6162F5] text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Click me</button>

// ✅ GOOD
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
<Button variant="default">Click me</Button>
```
